xcons
=====

- resolve exit error
- handle delete key
- handle pasting selection
- read-only mode
- decide how to handle e.g. '\b \b' from host
- populate with only last (n)KB of data

consd
=====

- save output to log file
- load existing log file on start-up
- rotate log files at midnight
- use identd to identify client
- permission list per host
- refuse input if not in list
